keyword><keyword weight="0.50893">Program analysis</keyword><keyword weight="0.48727">Soundness</keyword><keyword weight="0.44026">Calculus</keyword><keyword weight="0.49589">Modal</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We present Kripke modal transition systems (Kripke MTSs), a generalization of modal transition systems [27, 26], as a foundation for three-valued program analysis. The semantics of Kripke MTSs are presented by means of a mixed power domain of states; soundness and consistency are proved. Two major applications, model checking partial state spaces and three-valued program shape analysis, are presented as evidence of the suitability of Kripke MTSs as a foundation for three-valued analyses.</abstract></paper>